In the Matter of Isidore WEISEL, Bankrupt. Isidore Weisel, Bankrupt-Appellant, Jacob Goldberg, Carrie Goldberg and Henry Levy, Creditors-Appellees. No. 339. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. May 3, 1937. Sidney M. Wittner, of New York City, for appellant. Appel & Tannenbaum, of New York City (Alexander Appel and Harry A. Tif-ford, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellees.

Before MANTON, SWAN, and AUGUSTUS N. HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed.
